hpnicfWIPS.name: hpnicfWIPS

revisions.description: The initial revision of this MIB module.

hpnicfWIPS.description: This MIB provides information about WIPS feature. Wireless Intrusion Prevention System (WIPS) WIPS is designed to be employed in an area that is serviced by an existing wireless network. It aids in the early detection of malicious outsider attacks and intrusions via wireless networks, and takes corresponding measures in order to guarantee the wireless environment security.

HpnicfWIPSRadioType.name: HpnicfWIPSRadioType
HpnicfWIPSRadioType.description: Represents AP 802.11 radio type of 802.11a/b/g/n as per the standard. The following values are supported: dot11a - 802.11a dot11b - 802.11b dot11g - 802.11g dot11n - 802.11n dot11gn - 802.11gn dot11an - 802.11an

HpnicfWIPSEncryptMethod.name: HpnicfWIPSEncryptMethod
HpnicfWIPSEncryptMethod.description: Represents the frame encryption cipher types for frames on IEEE 802.11 radio interfaces. The MIB defines TC by referring to the 802.11i protocol. The following values are supported: none(1) - clear text or no cipher method is configure, wep(2) - WEP key, tkip(4) - WPA Temporal Key encryption, ccmp(8) - WPA AES CCMP encryption

HpnicfWIPSAuthMethod.description: Represents the key management mode defined by 802.11i. The following values are supported: none - No key management mode configured, psk - pre-shared key authentication, dot1x - 802.1x authentication. other - other authentication.

hpnicfWIPSAPAuthType.description: Represents the authentication type of the AP. undo - represents undo operation

hpnicfWIPSMaxRSSIValue.name: hpnicfWIPSMaxRSSIValue
hpnicfWIPSMaxRSSIValue.description: Represents the high-limit of the RSSI of AP. Available value limits from 1 to 90.

hpnicfWIPSAtkDctPolicyCfgSupportSet.name: hpnicfWIPSAtkDctPolicyCfgSupportSet
hpnicfWIPSAtkDctPolicyCfgSupportSet.description: Represents the bit string of supported attack detect policy. The specific attack detect policy is supported if its corresponding bit is set to 1; otherwise its corresponding bit is set to 0. bit0: adhoc bit1: ap-spoof bit2: client-spoof bit3: prohibited channel bit4: ap-flood bit5: eapol-start bit6: authentication bit7: association bit8: reassociation bit9: weak-IV bit10: invalid-OUI

hpnicfWIPSAtkDctPolicyDosReAssoQT.description: Represents the quiet time after reporting the dos of reassociation attack event alarm.

hpnicfWIPSIgnoreListRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

hpnicfWIPSDctModeTable.description: The table represents the list of AP scanning mode configuration on radio.

hpnicfWIPSDctModeEntry.name: hpnicfWIPSDctModeEntry
hpnicfWIPSDctModeEntry.description: Each entry contains information of WIPS scanning mode on radio.

hpnicfWIPSDctModeScanMode.description: Represents the scanning mode. The radio enable-disable status must be disabled before WIPS scanning mode is configured on this radio. The mesh feature must be disabled before any WIPS scanning mode is set on radio. This radio can not apply any service template before the detectOnly scanning mode is set on the radio.

hpnicfWIPSSigRule2PolicyEntry.description: Each entry contains information of each signature rules attached to signature policy.

hpnicfWIPSSigRule2PolicySigRuleIDCfg.description: Represents the ID of signature rule attached to signature policy.

hpnicfWIPSSigRule2PolicyPrecedence.description: Represents the precedence of signature rule attached to signature policy.

hpnicfWIPSSigRuleTable.name: hpnicfWIPSSigRuleTable
hpnicfWIPSSigRuleTable.description: The table defines the signature rules.

hpnicfWIPSSigRuleEntry.name: hpnicfWIPSSigRuleEntry
hpnicfWIPSSigRuleEntry.description: Each entry contains information of each signature rules.

hpnicfWIPSSigRuleName.name: hpnicfWIPSSigRuleName
hpnicfWIPSSigRuleName.description: Represents the name of signature rule.

hpnicfWIPSSigRuleID.name: hpnicfWIPSSigRuleID
hpnicfWIPSSigRuleID.description: Represents the ID of signature rule. The values from 1 to 32 are for built-in rules, which can not be assigned to user-define rules. When a user-define signature rule is being created, if ID is not specified, the ID of the rule will be automatically assigned, which values from 33 to 64. Once the rule is created, the ID is fixed and can not be changed again.

hpnicfWIPSSigRuleRowStatus.name: hpnicfWIPSSigRuleRowStatus
hpnicfWIPSSigRuleRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

hpnicfWIPSSigSubRuleMatchAll.name: hpnicfWIPSSigSubRuleMatchAll
hpnicfWIPSSigSubRuleMatchAll.description: Represents whether match all the sub rules which have been configured in the signature rule. The default value for user-define rule is false, and for built-in rule is true.

hpnicfWIPSSigRuleDctPeriod.name: hpnicfWIPSSigRuleDctPeriod
hpnicfWIPSSigRuleDctPeriod.description: Represents the detect period of signature rule. Available value limits from 1 to 3600. The default value depends on the certain rule. For user-define rules it is 60. The value 0xffffffff represents restoring default value operation.

hpnicfWIPSSigRuleTrackMethod.name: hpnicfWIPSSigRuleTrackMethod
hpnicfWIPSSigRuleTrackMethod.description: Represents the track-method for the signature rule. The default value depends on the certain rule. For user-define rules it is 'both(3)'.

hpnicfWIPSSigRuleDctThresholdPerMAC.name: hpnicfWIPSSigRuleDctThresholdPerMAC
hpnicfWIPSSigRuleDctThresholdPerMAC.description: Represents the detect threshold for per-MAC track-method. Available value limits from 1 to 32000. The default value depends on the certain rule. For user-define rules it is 1000. The value 0xffffffff represents restoring default value operation.

hpnicfWIPSSigRuleDctThresholdPerSig.name: hpnicfWIPSSigRuleDctThresholdPerSig
hpnicfWIPSSigRuleDctThresholdPerSig.description: Represents the detect threshold for per-Signature track-method. Available value limits from 1 to 32000. The default value depends on the certain rule. For user-define rules it is 1000. The value 0xffffffff represents restoring default value operation.

hpnicfWIPSSigRuleActionEvtLevel.name: hpnicfWIPSSigRuleActionEvtLevel
hpnicfWIPSSigRuleActionEvtLevel.description: Represents the level of event sended for the action of reporting event alarm. Available value limits from 0 to 7. The default value depends on the certain rule. For user-define rules it is 0xffffffff.

hpnicfWIPSSigRuleQuietTime.name: hpnicfWIPSSigRuleQuietTime
hpnicfWIPSSigRuleQuietTime.description: Represents the quiet time after reporting event alarm. Available value limits from 60 to 32000. The default value depends on the certain rule. For user-define rules it is 900. The value 0xffffffff represents restoring default value operation.

hpnicfWIPSSigSubRuleFrameType.name: hpnicfWIPSSigSubRuleFrameType
hpnicfWIPSSigSubRuleFrameType.description: Represents the type of frame to match. 0x0 management type 0x1 control type 0x2 data type The default value depends on the certain rule. For user-define rules it is 'undo(3)'.

hpnicfWIPSSigSubRuleFrameSubType.name: hpnicfWIPSSigSubRuleFrameSubType
hpnicfWIPSSigSubRuleFrameSubType.description: Represents the sub-type of frame to match. 1 association request 2 association response 3 probe request 4 beacon 5 disassoc 6 authentication 7 de-authentication The default value depends on the certain rule. For user-define rules it is 'none(0)'.

hpnicfWIPSSigSubRuleMac.name: hpnicfWIPSSigSubRuleMac
hpnicfWIPSSigSubRuleMac.description: Represents the MAC address or BSSID to match.

hpnicfWIPSSigSubRuleMacType.name: hpnicfWIPSSigSubRuleMacType
hpnicfWIPSSigSubRuleMacType.description: Represents the type of MAC address or BSSID to match. 0 Source MAC address in the 802.11 frame header 1 Destination MAC address in the 802.11 frame header 2 BSSID field in the 802.11 frame header

hpnicfWIPSSigSubRuleSeqNumMin.name: hpnicfWIPSSigSubRuleSeqNumMin
hpnicfWIPSSigSubRuleSeqNumMin.description: Represents the minimun value of sequence number of packet to match. Available value limits from 0 to 4094. The default value depends on the certain rule. For user-define rules it is 0xffffffff. The value 0xffffffff represents restoring default value operation.

hpnicfWIPSSigSubRuleSeqNumMax.name: hpnicfWIPSSigSubRuleSeqNumMax
hpnicfWIPSSigSubRuleSeqNumMax.description: Represents the maximum value of sequence number of packet to match. Available value limits from 1 to 4095. The default value depends on the certain rule. For user-define rules it is 0xffffffff. The value 0xffffffff represents restoring default value operation.

hpnicfWIPSSigSubRuleSSIDLenMin.name: hpnicfWIPSSigSubRuleSSIDLenMin
hpnicfWIPSSigSubRuleSSIDLenMin.description: Represents the minimun value of SSID of packet to match. Available value limits from 0 to 31. The default value depends on the certain rule. For user-define rules it is 0xffffffff. The value 0xffffffff represents restoring default value operation.

hpnicfWIPSSigSubRuleSSIDLenMax.name: hpnicfWIPSSigSubRuleSSIDLenMax
hpnicfWIPSSigSubRuleSSIDLenMax.description: Represents the maximum value of SSID of packet to match. Available value limits from 1 to 32. The default value depends on the certain rule. For user-define rules it is 0xffffffff. The value 0xffffffff represents restoring default value operation.

hpnicfWIPSSigSubRuleSSID.name: hpnicfWIPSSigSubRuleSSID

hpnicfWIPSSigSubRuleSSIDOpe.name: hpnicfWIPSSigSubRuleSSIDOpe

hpnicfWIPSSigSubRuleSSIDCase.name: hpnicfWIPSSigSubRuleSSIDCase
hpnicfWIPSSigSubRuleSSIDCase.description: Represents the case sensitive or not for the SSID match. 'true': Case insensitive. 'false': Case sensitive.

hpnicfWIPSSigSubRulePatternTable.description: The table defines the signature sub rules which define the user-define match way through pattern of packet.

hpnicfWIPSSigSubRulePatternEntry.name: hpnicfWIPSSigSubRulePatternEntry
hpnicfWIPSSigSubRulePatternEntry.description: Each entry contains information of each pattern signature sub rules.

hpnicfWIPSSigSubRulePatternID.name: hpnicfWIPSSigSubRulePatternID
hpnicfWIPSSigSubRulePatternID.description: Represents the ID of the pattern sub rule.

hpnicfWIPSSigSubRuleRowStatus.name: hpnicfWIPSSigSubRuleRowStatus

hpnicfWIPSSigSubRulePatternName.name: hpnicfWIPSSigSubRulePatternName

hpnicfWIPSSigSubRulePatternMask.name: hpnicfWIPSSigSubRulePatternMask

hpnicfWIPSSigSubRulePatternValueMin.description: Represents the minimun value of match byte. Available value limits from 0 to 65534.

hpnicfWIPSSigSubRulePatternFromPayload.name: hpnicfWIPSSigSubRulePatternFromPayload

hpnicfWIPSCtmPolicyUnauthStaPre.name: hpnicfWIPSCtmPolicyUnauthStaPre

hpnicfWIPSStaticTrustVendorListCfgEntry.description: Each entry contains information of each vendor in the static trust list.

hpnicfWIPSDctAPEntry.description: Each entry contains possible BSS information of each AP detected by WIPS.

hpnicfWIPSDctAPVSD.description: Represents the virtual security domain where the BSS was detected.

hpnicfWIPSDctAPEncryptMethod.name: hpnicfWIPSDctAPEncryptMethod
hpnicfWIPSDctAPEncryptMethod.description: Represents the encrypt method used by the detected AP. none(1) - clear text or no cipher method is configure, wep(2) - WEP key, tkip(4) - WPA Temporal Key encryption, ccmp(8) - WPA AES CCMP encryption
